**Review Findings (chain-verification)**

**Critical**
1. Reserved chain fields can be poisoned via mixed key forms before checksum generation.
- Evidence: [`audit.ex:21`](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app/audit.ex:21), [`audit.ex:169`](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app/audit.ex:169), [`chain.ex:96`](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app/audit/chain.ex:96)
- Impact: user-supplied `"account_id"` / `"sequence_number"` can collide with injected atom keys and corrupt checksum determinism.
- Triage: `td-ad5fd3` (P1 bug)

**Warnings**
2. Sequence-gap reporting can allocate unbounded memory on large jumps.
- Evidence: [`verifier.ex:72`](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app/audit/verifier.ex:72)
- Impact: very large tampered/corrupt sequence jumps can blow memory via `Enum.to_list/1`.
- Triage: `td-c1fa7f` (P2 bug)

3. Missing regression test for non-`:no_entries` checkpoint failure while continuing other accounts.
- Evidence: [`checkpoint-worker spec:15`](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/openspec/changes/chain-verification/specs/checkpoint-worker/spec.md:15), [`checkpoint_worker.ex:60`](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app/audit/checkpoint_worker.ex:60), [`checkpoint_worker_test.exs:10`](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/test/app/audit/checkpoint_worker_test.exs:10)
- Triage: `td-14992f` (P2 task)

**Suggestion**
4. Set explicit checkpoint worker interval in test config for deterministic behavior.
- Evidence: [`application.ex:17`](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app/application.ex:17), [`checkpoint_worker.ex:16`](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/lib/app/audit/checkpoint_worker.ex:16), [`test.exs:1`](/Users/tbrewer/projects/goodway/goodaudit/app/config/test.exs:1)
